 a reference to external API documentation in the 設定方法 section that the knowledge file doesn't include, but since it's just a link to another document rather than the actual API details, it's acceptable to omit. The source shows a JavaScript-commented JSON example with a truncated error message output, and the knowledge file correctly converted it to valid JSON without comments, which aligns with the source's explicit note that actual JSON files can't contain comments. The knowledge file also synthesizes the verifier class descriptions from the JSON comments into a helpful table format, which is a reasonable interpretation of the source material. Let me verify the s3 section more carefully to ensure the error output was captured accurately. Now I'm verifying that the s9 section about TagAttributeVerifier meets the length requirements, and doing a final review of the knowledge file structure. Let me trace through the s2 section again to make sure all the setup steps are properly documented—Node.js installation, proxy configuration, npm verification, and the configuration file modifications. The knowledge file appears to be in good shape overall. I'm reconsidering the section count warning though — it's flagging 9 sections against 13 source headings, but looking at the RST structure, the content is appropriately consolidated. The h2 sections stay under the 2000 character limit and the hierarchical organization makes sense, so this isn't actually a structural problem that needs fixing. 方法, 設定方法 (4 sections)\n- h2 sections (underline with `=`): Node.jsのインストール, 環境変数の確認, 依存パッケージのインストール, 正常に使用できることの確認, 環境依存設定値の修正, batファイルでの実行, コマンドラインからの実行, 既定の設定内容 (8 sections)\n- h3 sections (underline with `-`): 使用可能タグ検証, 正規表現検証, DOMツリー検証, 親タグ検証, タグ属性検証 (5 sections)\n\nTotal = 4 + 8 + 5 = 17 headings\n\nThe automated check reported 13 headings, though the knowledge file itself has 9 sections. The V3 validation checks whether h2 sections with 2000+ characters of plain text that contain h3